INSERT INTO `comments` VALUES (1,'This is one of the most balanced takes on AI I have read in months. The point about explainability being a prerequisite for trust really resonated with me.','2025-10-11 10:00:00.000000',_binary '\0',1,12),(2,'Great overview, though I think the timeline for AGI is far more uncertain than even the cautious estimates suggest. We are still nowhere near human-level general reasoning.','2025-10-13 14:30:00.000000',_binary '\0',1,22),(3,'The displacement question keeps me up at night. My entire department could theoretically be automated within three years and nobody is talking about it seriously.','2025-10-20 09:15:00.000000',_binary '\0',1,35),(4,'Kubernetes has genuinely changed how we operate at my company. The learning curve is steep but the operational maturity it enables is worth it.','2025-10-18 11:30:00.000000',_binary '\0',2,17),(5,'Would love a follow-up focused specifically on database scalability strategies — that is always the bottleneck nobody prepares for early enough.','2025-10-23 13:00:00.000000',_binary '\0',2,30),(6,'Flutter has been a game-changer for our small team. We ship features to iOS and Android simultaneously and the widget system makes custom UI a joy to build.','2025-10-22 09:45:00.000000',_binary '\0',3,19),(7,'On-device AI inference is still far from production-ready on low-end Android devices. The article is slightly optimistic on that front.','2025-10-27 14:00:00.000000',_binary '\0',3,28),(8,'FinOps is something more engineering teams need to take seriously. We were burning $40K a month on idle resources before someone finally audited our AWS bills.','2025-10-28 10:30:00.000000',_binary '\0',4,21),(9,'The shared responsibility model section is exactly what I will share with our executive team. They still think moving to the cloud means someone else handles security.','2025-11-02 11:00:00.000000',_binary '\0',4,34),(10,'The emphasis on model drift is so important and so underrepresented in introductory ML content. Most tutorials stop at validation accuracy as if deployment does not exist.','2025-11-03 10:15:00.000000',_binary '\0',5,23),(11,'Fairness and interpretability deserve a dedicated article. They are deep enough topics that a paragraph each does not do justice to the complexity involved.','2025-11-07 13:30:00.000000',_binary '\0',5,40),(12,'The topological qubit angle is fascinating. Microsoft has been betting on this approach for over a decade and it finally seems to be approaching tangible results.','2025-11-08 09:00:00.000000',_binary '\0',6,26),(13,'Post-quantum cryptography cannot come soon enough. Our organization is already inventorying our cryptographic assets to prepare for the migration.','2025-11-14 14:00:00.000000',_binary '\0',6,42),(14,'The framing around Scope 3 emissions is well done. Most climate commitments look weak once you account for the full supply chain footprint.','2025-11-13 10:00:00.000000',_binary '\0',7,29),(15,'I appreciate the balance here. Adaptation is still treated as giving up in many policy circles when it is actually an essential parallel track to mitigation.','2025-11-17 12:45:00.000000',_binary '\0',7,50),(16,'The section on neuroplasticity aligns with what I have observed in cognitive rehabilitation. The brain\'s ability to reorganize even after significant injury is remarkable.','2025-11-18 09:30:00.000000',_binary '\0',8,31),(17,'The cost-per-kg drop from reusability has been genuinely transformational. It is easy to forget how recently this was considered impossible by most of the industry.','2025-11-23 11:00:00.000000',_binary '\0',9,32),(18,'Space law is the real wildcard here. The Outer Space Treaty was not designed for commercial actors and the gaps are becoming more obvious with every Starlink launch.','2025-11-28 14:30:00.000000',_binary '\0',9,45),(19,'The equity point is critical. If CRISPR therapies cost hundreds of thousands of dollars, they are essentially inaccessible to the populations who bear the highest disease burden.','2025-11-28 10:00:00.000000',_binary '\0',10,33),(20,'The distinction between somatic and germline editing is something the popular press consistently conflates. Thank you for being precise about it.','2025-12-02 13:00:00.000000',_binary '\0',10,54),(21,'The section on generative AI and authorship is the conversation the art world needs to have right now. The Christie\'s auction in 2018 barely scratched the surface.','2025-12-04 09:15:00.000000',_binary '\0',11,35),(22,'I have always found the conceptual art movement difficult to appreciate but this article gave me enough context to understand what it was reacting against. Well written.','2025-12-07 11:30:00.000000',_binary '\0',11,48),(23,'Substack has completely changed my reading habits. I now pay directly for six writers whose work I would never have found through traditional publishing pipelines.','2025-12-07 10:30:00.000000',_binary '\0',12,37),(24,'The question of what forms are native to networked media is one I think about constantly as someone who writes serialized fiction online. The tools barely exist yet.','2025-12-12 14:00:00.000000',_binary '\0',12,60),(25,'K-pop\'s global rise is a genuinely interesting case study in how strategic cultural production combined with fan community architecture can cross language barriers.','2025-12-13 10:00:00.000000',_binary '\0',13,39),(26,'The algorithmic bubble point is real. My Spotify recommendations became almost claustrophobically narrow until I started actively seeking out new genres manually.','2025-12-17 12:30:00.000000',_binary '\0',13,52),(27,'Bong Joon-ho is a perfect example of how cinema can work simultaneously as popular entertainment and serious social critique without either quality undercutting the other.','2025-12-18 09:45:00.000000',_binary '\0',14,40),(28,'The creator economy point cuts both ways. Yes it democratizes fame, but it also forces creators to become marketers and data analysts, which erodes time for the actual creative work.','2025-12-23 11:00:00.000000',_binary '\0',15,41),(29,'The observation about diaspora networks is underappreciated. The connections between Silicon Valley and Lagos or Nairobi are genuinely driving capital and mentorship flows back.','2026-01-08 09:30:00.000000',_binary '\0',16,43),(30,'Remote work decoupling founders from hubs is interesting in theory but investor networks are still highly geographically concentrated. Has that actually changed in practice?','2026-01-12 13:00:00.000000',_binary '\0',16,62),(31,'The behavioral discipline section is the most important and the least glamorous part of investing. Most people would be better served by automating contributions and ignoring their portfolio.','2026-01-13 10:15:00.000000',_binary '\0',17,46),(32,'The case for low-cost index funds has been made so thoroughly by now that the active management industry\'s continued existence is essentially a tribute to marketing over evidence.','2026-01-18 14:30:00.000000',_binary '\0',17,70),(33,'The asynchronous communication culture point is the one thing most organizations get wrong. Defaulting to a meeting for everything that used to happen in an office is not the same as thriving remotely.','2026-01-18 10:00:00.000000',_binary '\0',18,48),(34,'Our team moved to fully async with a four-hour overlap window and productivity genuinely increased. The documentation culture alone is worth the adjustment period.','2026-01-22 12:45:00.000000',_binary '\0',18,75),(35,'The packaging waste problem is enormous and largely invisible to consumers. I would love to see extended producer responsibility legislation applied seriously to e-commerce.','2026-01-23 11:00:00.000000',_binary '\0',19,49),(36,'Scope 3 disclosure requirements are going to be the biggest compliance challenge for most supply chains over the next five years. Most companies have no idea where to start.','2026-01-28 09:30:00.000000',_binary '\0',20,50),(37,'The shift to product-as-service models is genuinely exciting. When a manufacturer profits from product longevity rather than replacement cycles, the incentives finally align with sustainability.','2026-02-02 13:00:00.000000',_binary '\0',20,80),(38,'The point about stigma being the prerequisite is so true. Until people can name what they are experiencing without shame, all the expanded services in the world will go unused.','2026-02-04 10:00:00.000000',_binary '\0',21,51),(39,'Workplace mental health programs are mostly theater at the companies I have worked for. Real change requires workload reduction and manager accountability, not free meditation apps.','2026-02-08 14:15:00.000000',_binary '\0',21,63),(40,'The industry funding point deserves to be screamed from rooftops. The correlation between sugar-industry-funded research and findings exonerating sugar is not coincidental.','2026-02-11 09:45:00.000000',_binary '\0',22,54),(41,'Continuous glucose monitors changed how I understand my own body\'s response to different foods. The personalization angle is real even if the evidence base is still catching up.','2026-02-15 12:00:00.000000',_binary '\0',22,72),(42,'The VO2 max finding was striking when I first read the underlying paper. It genuinely predicts longevity better than almost any other biomarker we can measure non-invasively.','2026-02-18 10:30:00.000000',_binary '\0',23,56),(43,'The chronotype point is one I wish my employer understood. I am categorically not a morning person and forcing 9am standups has measurable costs to my cognitive output.','2026-02-25 09:00:00.000000',_binary '\0',24,57),(44,'The data on how quickly cognitive impairment accumulates from sleep restriction is sobering. We treat sleep deprivation as a badge of honor when it should be treated as an injury.','2026-03-01 13:30:00.000000',_binary '\0',24,85),(45,'The distinction between structured MBSR programs and casual app usage in clinical outcomes matches my own experience. Ten minutes of guided audio is not the same as intentional practice.','2026-03-04 10:15:00.000000',_binary '\0',25,58);
